 
ALGORITHM 
 
Step1: Start the HTML document. 
Step 2: Use <img> tag to embed images. 
Step 3: Use <audio> tag with controls to add audio. 
Step 4: Use <video> tag with controls to embed video. 
Step 5: Add necessary src, type, and styling attributes. 
Step 6: Save the file with .html extension. 
Step 7: Open the file in a browser to view the multimedia content. 

Correct Multimedia HTML Code (multimedia.html)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Multimedia Demo</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #003366;
        }
        .media-section {
            border: 2px solid #0077b6;
            background-color: #e0f7fa;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            width: 80%;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        img {
            width: 300px;
            height: auto;
            border: 2px solid #004d99;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Multimedia Content in Website</h1>

    <div class="media-section">
        <h2>Image</h2>
        <img src="sample.jpg" alt="Sample Image">
    </div>

    <div class="media-section">
        <h2>Audio</h2>
        <audio controls>
            <source src="sample.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
            Your browser does not support the audio tag.
        </audio>
    </div>

    <div class="media-section">
        <h2>Video</h2>
        <video width="320" height="240" controls>
            <source src="sample.mp4" type="video/mp4">
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
        </video>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
